quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,50,"Say, “Be you stones or iron<sup>43</sup>,","[43] i.e., even if you could be stones or iron in hardness or in power."
  17,51,"or any other substance you think is harder<sup>44</sup> to bring back to life.” They will then say, “Who will bring us back [to life]?” Say, “The One Who created you the first time.” They will shake their heads<sup>45</sup> at you and say, “When will that be?” Say, “Perhaps it is soon.”","[44] Such as the heavens and the earth.\n [45] In ridicule and disbelief."
  17,52,"On the Day when He calls you, you will respond by praising Him, thinking that you had not stayed [on earth] except for a little while.",""
  17,53,"Tell My slaves that they should say what is best<sup>46</sup>, for Satan sows discord among them. Indeed, Satan is a sworn enemy to mankind.","[46] i.e., they should be considerate and kind, well-spoken, and tolerant to win hearts."
  17,54,"Your Lord knows you best: if He wills, He will have mercy on you; or if He wills, He will punish you. We have not sent you [O Prophet] to be in charge of them<sup>47</sup>.","[47] The mission of the Prophet (ﷺ) was only delivering the Message; their guidance and holding to account is up to Allah Almighty."
  17,55,"Your Lord knows best all those in the heavens and on earth<sup>48</sup>. We have surely favored some prophets over others, and We gave David the Psalms<sup>49</sup>.","[48] Allah knows all and what they deserve.\n [49] Al-Zabūr is revealed to Prophet David (عليه السلام); al-zabūr (pl. zubūr) originally is every book that contains wisdom. See 3:184."
  17,56,"Say, “Call upon those whom you claimed [to be gods] besides Him; they have no power to remove harm or avert it from you.”",""
  17,57,"Those whom they call upon seek means of nearness to their Lord, each trying to become closer, hoping for His Mercy and fearing His punishment<sup>50</sup>. Indeed, the punishment of your Lord is fearsome.","[50] Such as angels, prophets, righteous believers, etc."
  17,58,"There is no [disbelieving] town except that We will destroy it before the Day of Resurrection or punish it severely<sup>51</sup>. This is written in the Record<sup>52</sup>.","[51] Due to the disbelief and sins of its inhabitants. [52] i.e., the Preserved Tablet."
